      "side": 1,
      "message": "This sentinel-aware free path is only needed when TSO is enabled, because only TSO creates extra WQEBB slots marked RDMA_TXQ_INVALID_BUF. For non-TSO mlx5 TX, every completed ring slot should still contain a real buffer index, so we should keep the old vlib_buffer_free_from_ring() fast path there.\n\nCan we select the free helper based on TSO support, ideally in a way that lets the non-TSO path compile down to the old behavior?",
      "revId": "df30104bf8c489cbe0c7bf53c188518f826a25bb",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "19afc1ba_1a7429a7",
        "filename": "src/plugins/rdma/output.c",
